<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 14:40:56 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>保罗·狄拉克</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/paul-dirac</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 14:40:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/paul-dirac</guid></item><item><title>MR-AIV 通过基于物理的 AI 揭示体内全脑流体流动</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/mr-aiv-reveals-in-vivo-brain-wide-fluid-flow-with-physics-informed-ai</link><description>基于物理的人工智能通过 MRI 揭示脑液流动，这是了解大脑健康和神经系统疾病的关键。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/mr-aiv-reveals-in-vivo-brain-wide-fluid-flow-with-physics-informed-ai2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 14:25:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/mr-aiv-reveals-in-vivo-brain-wide-fluid-flow-with-physics-informed-ai</guid></item><item><title>durcabtagene autoleucel 在针对复发/难治性多发性骨髓瘤患者的 1 期试验中的疗效和安全性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/efficacy-and-safety-of-durcabtagene-autoleucel-in-a-phase-1-trial-for-patients-with-relapsed-refractory-multiple-myeloma</link><description>自体 CAR T 细胞疗法的生产时间过长可能与快速进展性疾病 (PD) 不相容，从而导致对桥接疗法的需求增加，以实现疾病稳定。临床试验中大多数接受 cilta-cel 和 ide-cel 治疗的患者（分别为 75% 和 87%）需要桥接治疗（ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/efficacy-and-safety-of-durcabtagene-autoleucel-in-a-phase-1-trial-for-patients-with-relapsed-refractory-multiple-myeloma2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 14:10:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/efficacy-and-safety-of-durcabtagene-autoleucel-in-a-phase-1-trial-for-patients-with-relapsed-refractory-multiple-myeloma</guid></item><item><title>量子近似优化算法在经典棘手问题上的缩放优势的证据</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/evidence-of-scaling-advantage-for-the-quantum-approximate-optimization-algorithm-on-a-classically-intractable-problem</link><description>我们研究了低自相关二进制序列 (LABS) 问题上 QAOA TTS 随问题大小的缩放（ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/evidence-of-scaling-advantage-for-the-quantum-approximate-optimization-algorithm-on-a-classically-intractable-problem2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 13:55:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/evidence-of-scaling-advantage-for-the-quantum-approximate-optimization-algorithm-on-a-classically-intractable-problem</guid></item><item><title>大综合（“奇点”或失落的原眼统一场）</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-grand-synthesis-singularity-or-lost-primal-eye-unified-field</link><description>大综合（“奇点”，或失落的原始之眼统一场）。我的工作跨越了近 50 年，涵盖了极其丰富的学科矩阵：进化生物学、心灵哲学、临床催眠疗法、神学。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-grand-synthesis-singularity-or-lost-primal-eye-unified-field.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 13:40:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-grand-synthesis-singularity-or-lost-primal-eye-unified-field</guid></item><item><title>螺旋声子结构超共振</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/coiled-phononic-structure-super-resonates</link><description>计算机模拟显示了放置在表面下方的结构如何抑制各种频率下流过表面的流体的湍流。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/coiled-phononic-structure-super-resonates.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 13:25:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/coiled-phononic-structure-super-resonates</guid></item><item><title>抛开重力：国际空间站的实验揭示了粒子如何改变湍流行为</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/leaving-gravity-behind-experiment-from-iss-reveals-how-particles-alter-turbulent-flow-behavior</link><description>在离开地球数百英里并在国际空间站上呆了几个月后，特拉华大学的一项实验返回校园，带来了有关微重力下湍流行为的新数据。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/leaving-gravity-behind-experiment-from-iss-reveals-how-particles-alter-turbulent-flow-behavior.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 13:10:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/leaving-gravity-behind-experiment-from-iss-reveals-how-particles-alter-turbulent-flow-behavior</guid></item><item><title>火蚁集体中的涟漪表明运动是由邻居排列驱动的</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ripples-in-fire-ant-collectives-suggest-motions-are-driven-by-neighbor-alignments</link><description>西班牙的研究人员发现，在移动的火蚁群体中，密度和活动的涟漪“波”很可能是由局部区域引发的，在该区域中，蚂蚁集体沿着与邻居相同的方向移动。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ripples-in-fire-ant-collectives-suggest-motions-are-driven-by-neighbor-alignments2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 12:55:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ripples-in-fire-ant-collectives-suggest-motions-are-driven-by-neighbor-alignments</guid></item><item><title>用于计算的自旋波信号在 Z 形路径方法中增强了 5,000 倍以上</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/spin-wave-signals-used-in-computing-boosted-more-than-5000-times-in-z-shaped-path-approach</link><description>来自东北大学、信越化学株式会社和洛桑联邦理工学院 (EPFL) 的研究团队发明了一种新方法，可以以最小的损耗有效引导自旋波绕过尖角，这代表了节能计算方面的一项令人兴奋的发现。研究小组使用二维镁振子晶体（一种放置在磁性石榴石薄膜上的带有六角形微孔阵列的铜 (Cu) 薄膜），通过计算表明，自旋波沿着 Z 形路径传播的效率比传统波导高 5,000 倍以上。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/spin-wave-signals-used-in-computing-boosted-more-than-5000-times-in-z-shaped-path-approach2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 12:40:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/spin-wave-signals-used-in-computing-boosted-more-than-5000-times-in-z-shaped-path-approach</guid></item><item><title>量子电子学研究指出了未来的能源和计算技术</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/quantum-vibronics-research-points-to-future-energy-and-computing-technologies</link><description>加州大学河滨分校的科学家在理解量子波函数如何在超薄材料上移动方面取得了突破，这项研究最终可能会改进太阳能技术，并有助于为新形式的量子计算奠定基础。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/quantum-vibronics-research-points-to-future-energy-and-computing-technologies.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 12:25:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/quantum-vibronics-research-points-to-future-energy-and-computing-technologies</guid></item></channel></rss>